{"id":"256590425_The_moment_generating_function_has_its_moments","abstract":"Traditionally, the moment generating function of a random variable X, is used to generate (positive integer) moments of X. However, moments of quite general transformations of X can be obtained by judicious differentiations and weighted integration of the moment generating function. The particular case of Xγ, −∞<γ<∞, is treated in detail, and applications are given.","authors":["Noel Cressie","Marinus Borkent"],"meta":["April 1986Journal of Statistical Planning and Inference 13(3):337–344","DOI:10.1016/0378-3758(86)90143-6"],"references":["268785887_The_use_of_fractional_calculus_in_probability","270482956_Comment_on_Estimating_Mixtures_of_Normal_Distributions_and_Switching_Regressions","267119840_Remarks_on_the_Relation_between_Fractional_Moments_and_Fractional_Derivatives_of_Characteristic_Functions","267118234_Introduction_to_Mathematical_Statistics","265332299_The_fractional_calculus_Theory_and_applications_of_differentiation_and_integration_to_arbitrary_order","256590155_Estimation_of_the_inverse_of_mean","254285578_High-Efficiency_Estimation_for_the_Positive_Stable_Laws","241735598_The_Use_of_Fractional_Moments_for_Estimating_the_Parameters_of_a_Mixed_Exponential_Distribution","241735314_The_Moment-Generating_Function_and_Negative_Integer_Moments","226845798_Robust_estimation_of_the_variogram_I","224043320_Handbook_of_Matematical_Functions","41753979_On_the_Fractional_Calculus_On_Fractional_Calculus_and_Its_Applications","31615766_Introduction_to_mathematical_statistics_RV_Hogg","7203036_The_Distribution_of_Chi-Square"]}